<subSubSection id="C374652CFF98FFF3D4CCF9FB09D7F920" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BD136A7FF98FFF3D4CCF9FB09D7F920" blockId="101.[151,1437,1472,2039]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FF98FFF3D4CCF9FB0C1AF9F9" bold="true" box="[199,322,1616,1642]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D24FF98FFF3D5BAF9FB0F22F9F9" authority="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Quijano, 2022" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Quijano" authorityYear="2022" box="[433,634,1616,1642]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Tenedos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yurayaco" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FF98FFF3D5BAF9FB0F22F9F9" box="[433,634,1616,1642]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Tenedos yurayaco</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FF98FFF3D68AF9FB0F98F9F9" bold="true" box="[641,704,1616,1642]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22957CEFF98FFF3D68AF9FB0F98F9F9" box="[641,704,1616,1642]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, can be distinguished by bifid retrolateral tibial apophysis (RTA), with thin and pointed anterior branch (aRTA), curved, long posterior branch (pRTA); median apophysis (MA) with concave anterior branch (aMA); very short posterior branch (pMA) (
<figureCitation id="13552A22FF98FFF3D793F9330978F921" box="[920,1056,1688,1714]" captionStart="FIGURE 72" captionStartId="102.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[175,1398,633,1947]" captionTargetId="figure-225@102.[175,1413,633,1952]" captionTargetPageId="102" captionText="FIGURE 72. Tenedos yurayaco sp. n. A–B. Male habits (IAvH-I-44): A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C–F. Male palp: C. Ventral view. D. Prolateral. E. Retroventral view. F. Retrolateral view. Scale bars: A–B: 2mm; C–F: 500µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520954" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520954/files/figure.png" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Figs 72C–F</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="13552A22FF98FFF3D027F93309DAF920" box="[1068,1154,1688,1715]" captionStart="FIGURE 75" captionStartId="106.[151,250,1438,1462]" captionTargetBox="[159,1432,185,1414]" captionTargetId="figure-27@106.[151,1436,181,1415]" captionTargetPageId="106" captionText="FIGURE 75. Tenedos yurayaco sp. n. A, D. Male palp (IAvH-I-44):A. Ventral view. D. Retrolateral view. Tenedos marquetones sp. n. B, E. Male palp (IAvH-I-2973): B. Ventral view. E. Retrolateral view. Tenedos pensilvania sp. n. C, F. Male palp (IAvH- I-657): C. Ventral view. F. Retrolateral view. Scale bars: A–F: 200µm. Abbreviations: aMA, anterior branch of the median apophysis; bRTA, basal retrolateral tibial apophysis; pMA, posterior branch of the median; apophysis; pRTA, posterior branch of the retrolateral tibial apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520960" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520960/files/figure.png" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">75A, D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
